<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Manipur</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">The <em>Jewel of India</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Manipur, the "Jewel of India," is a northeastern state renowned for its breathtaking natural beauty, vibrant culture and classical performing arts. Nestled in verdant valleys surrounded by majestic hills, Manipur captivates with serene lakes, pristine rivers and lush forests. Known as the "Land of Dance," Manipur is the birthplace of the world-famous Manipuri dance, a UNESCO-recognized art form expressing grace and spirituality. From the magnificent Loktak Lake with its floating islands to the sacred Shri Govardhan Temple, from bustling Imphal city to tranquil villages, Manipur offers diverse experiences. The state's rich martial arts traditions, intricate handicrafts, colorful festivals and authentic cuisine showcase Northeast India's cultural wealth. Manipur's commitment to preserving its heritage while embracing modern development creates a unique destination where ancient traditions thrive alongside contemporary life.</p>
</section>

